5 building in a school year for instructional purposes must be at
6 least thirty percent (30%) of:
7 (A) the known classroom design capacity of the school
8 building; or
9 (B) if the design capacity is not known, the average maximum
10 full-time equivalent enrollment in any of the last twenty-five
11 (25) years, as validated by records created or maintained by
12 the department; and
13 (if multiple school buildings are used for the same purposes)
